# {{brand.nameEscaped}}

> {{brand.taglineEscaped}}

Static-export Next.js 14 marketing site. Generated by [`@fixedcode/bundle-next-marketing-site`](https://github.com/gibbon/fixedcode/tree/master/bundles/next-marketing-site).

## Develop

```bash
npm install
npm run dev    # http://localhost:3000
```

## Build

```bash
npm run build  # writes static HTML/CSS/JS to ./out
```

The site is a pure static export (`output: 'export'`). Drop `out/` on any static host: Cloudflare Pages, Vercel, Netlify, S3, GitHub Pages, nginx, etc.

## Deploy

### Cloudflare Pages / Netlify / Vercel
- Build command: `npm run build`
- Output directory: `out`

{{#if hasDocker}}### Docker (nginx)
```bash
docker build -t {{appName.kebab}} .
docker run --rm -p 8080:80 {{appName.kebab}}
```

{{/if}}{{#if hasAnalytics}}## Analytics

This site is wired for **{{analytics}}** analytics. Copy `.env.example` → `.env.local` and fill in the values; the snippet is loaded from `app/layout.tsx`.

{{/if}}## Pages

| Path | Source | Owned by |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `/` | `app/page.tsx` | you (extension point) |
{{#each pages}}| `/{{slug}}/` | `app/{{slug}}/page.tsx` | you (extension point) |
{{/each}}

The landing page and each additional page are generated once and then user-owned — regenerating with `fixedcode generate` will not overwrite them. The `Navbar`, `Hero`, `Footer` components and the project plumbing (`package.json`, `next.config.mjs`, etc.) are regenerated.

## Regenerating

```bash
fixedcode generate <your-spec>.yaml -o .
```

Files marked `overwrite: false` in `.fixedcode-manifest.json` are preserved.
